{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"356c5700-9b2c-4b96-94e2-a9c1c5f422d4","content":"Here's the correct attribute for each framework:\n\n| Framework | Attribute |\n|-----------|-----------|\n| **MSTest** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **xUnit** | `[Fact(Skip = \"reason\")]` or `[Theory(Skip = \"reason\")]` |\n| **NUnit** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **TUnit** | `[Skip(\"reason\")]` |\n\n**Example usage:**\n\n```csharp\n// MSTest\n[TestMethod, Ignore(\"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyMsTest() { }\n\n// xUnit\n[Fact(Skip = \"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyXunitTest() { }\n\n// NUnit\n[Test, Ignore(\"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyNunitTest() { }\n\n// TUnit\n[Test, Skip(\"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic async Task MyTunitTest() { }\n```\n\nAll four will report the test as **skipped/ignored** (not failed) in test results, and the reason string appears in the test output.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"79195119-6e0c-4a80-bd80-ffcf09732c2b","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about test-skipping attributes across four .NET test frameworks. This is a knowledge question I can answer directly.","outputTokens":303,"requestId":"481B:286B29:776E60:89B582:69FBE704"},"id":"5c8804cc-8972-45af-b393-ac64e5fe52ab","timestamp":"2026-05-07T01:12:42.529Z","parentId":"25332152-605f-47d2-a6e1-2ad9ec9ddc41"}
